  "response": "Whether you should study Computer Science in Russia depends on several factors:\n\nPros:\n1. Lower tuition costs compared to Western countries\n2. Strong mathematical and theoretical computer science education\n3. Some universities have good reputation in technical education\n4. Opportunity to learn Russian language\n5. Potential for international exposure\n\nCons:\n1. Language barrier (many programs are in Russian)\n2. Current geopolitical tensions might complicate international study\n3. Limited English-taught programs\n4. Potentially different curriculum compared to Western standards\n5. Potential challenges with international job market recognition\n\nRecommendations:\n- Research specific universities (Moscow State University, Saint Petersburg State University)\n- Check program language of instruction\n- Verify degree recognition in your home country\n- Consider your career goals\n- Investigate current international student policies\n\nUltimately, the decision depends on your personal circumstances, language skills, financial situation, and career objectives. I recommend:\n- Consulting educational advisors\n- Comparing multiple international study options\n- Checking current geopolitical context\n- Verifying specific university's international reputation\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
